{"title_page": "MasterChef (American season 8)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television season\n |season_number = 8\n |bgcolour     = \n |image        = \n |caption      = \n |country      = United States\n |num_episodes = 21\n |network      = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n |first_aired  = {{Start date|2017|05|31}}\n |last_aired   = {{End date|2017|09|20}}\n |prev_season  = [[MasterChef (American season 7)|Season 7]]\n |next_season  = [[MasterChef (American season 9)|Season 9]]\n |episode_list = \n|}}\n\n'''Season 8''' of the American competitive [[reality television|reality TV]] series '''''[[MasterChef (American TV series)|MasterChef]]''''' premiered on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] on May 31, 2017.<ref name=\"futon\">{{cite web|title=FOX Announces Summer Premiere Dates|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2017/03/22/fox-announces-summer-premiere-dates-316121/20170322fox02/|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=April 4, 2017|date=March 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[Gordon Ramsay]] and [[Christina Tosi]] returned as judges. [[Aar\u00f3n Sanchez]] joined the cast this season as the third judge.<ref name=\"parade\">{{cite web|title=Chef Aar\u00f3n S\u00e1nchez Joins the MasterChef Judges' Panel |url=https://parade.com/548433/alison-ashton/chef-aaron-sanchez-joins-the-masterchef-judges-panel/|website=Parade|accessdate=April 25, 2017|date=February 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThis season was won by Dino Angelo Luciano with Eboni Henry and Jason Wang finishing as co-runners-up.\n\n==Top 20==\nSource for names, hometowns and occupations:<ref name=official-press-release-contestants>{{cite press release|url=http://www.fox.com/masterchef/article/meet-the-newest-batch-of-home-cooks| title=Meet the Newest Batch of Home Cooks|publisher= [[Fox Broadcasting]]|date= May 5, 2017|accessdate= June 11, 2017| archivedate= August 7, 2017| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20170807194436/http://www.fox.com/masterchef/article/meet-the-newest-batch-of-home-cooks}} Note: This supersedes an earlier press release with an incorrect name.</ref> Ages and nicknames as given on air.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#C1D8FF;\"\n! style=\"width:18%;\" |Contestant\n! style=\"width:4%;\"  |Age\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Hometown\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Occupation\n! style=\"width:16%;\" |Status\n|-\n| Dino Angelo Luciano\n| 28\n| [[Bensonhurst, New York]]\n| Dancer\n| style=\"background:green;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Winner September 20</span>\n|-\n| Eboni Henry\n| 33\n| [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| Addiction Counselor\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;\" rowspan=\"2\"|Runners-Up September 20\n|-\n| Jason Wang\n| 34\n| [[Newton, Massachusetts]]\n| High School Music Teacher\n|-\n| Caitlin \"Cate\" Meade\n| 25\n| Chicago, Illinois\n| Nutritionist\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |{{nowrap|Eliminated September 13}}\n|-\n| Jeff Philbin\n| 29\n| [[Tampa, Florida]]\n| Marketing Director\n|-\n| Yachecia Holston\n| 43\n| [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]]\n| Minister\n|-\n| Gabriel Lewis\n| 19\n| [[Oklahoma City, Oklahoma]]\n| Fast Food Server\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text-align:center;\" |{{nowrap|Eliminated September 6}}\n|-\n| Daniel Pontes-Macedo \n| 31\n| [[Medford, Massachusetts]]\n| Substitute Teacher\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |{{nowrap|Eliminated August 30}}\n|-\n| Caitlin Jones\n| 24\n| [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]]\n| Dancer\n|-\n| Adam Wong \n| 21\n| [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]]\n| Harvard Student\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |{{nowrap|Eliminated August 23}}\n|-\n| Jenny Cavellier\n| 25\n| [[Cincinnati, Ohio]]\n| Special Needs Therapist\n|-\n| Mike \"Newton\" Newton\n| 53\n| [[Lipan, Texas]]\n| Ranch Owner\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text-align:center;\" |{{nowrap|Eliminated August 16}}{{ref|1|1}}\n|-\n| Reba Billingsley\n| 48\n| [[Carthage, Texas]]\n| Stay-at-home Mom\n| style=\"