gs/wednesday-final-ratings-sept-6-2017/|title=\u2018Big Brother\u2019 adjusts up, \u2018Marlon\u2019 adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=September 8, 2017|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=September 8, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* '''Mystery Box Challenge:''' The mystery box contains chopsticks, as the contestants must make an Asian-inspired dish in 60 minutes. The top three dishes belong to Dino, Jason and Jeff, and Dino is the winner.\n* '''Challenge Winner/Immune:''' Dino Angelo Luciano\n* '''Pressure Test:''' The remaining contestants must make a homemade pasta dish, and Dino gets to choose which contestant cooks which style of pasta. He assigns pappardelle to Jason, farfalle to Eboni, cannelloni to Gabriel, cavatelli to Cate, tortellini to Yachecia, and egg yolk ravioli to Jeff. Eboni wins the challenge while Jason is also a top dish. Yachecia and Gabriel are called out as the bottom two.\n* '''Challenge Winner:''' Eboni Henry\n* '''Bottom two:''' Gabriel Lewis and Yachecia Holston\n* Gabriel is eliminated, but Gordon offers to send him to culinary school for training and Aar\u00f3n offers him a job in [[New Orleans]] once his training is done.\n* '''Eliminated:''' Gabriel Lewis\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 17\n| Title           = Pop-Up Restaurant\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|9|6}}\n| Viewers         = 3.80<ref name=\"8.16&8.17\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* '''Team Challenge:''' The contestants are taken to Triunfo Creek Vineyard where they are split into two teams. Eboni and Jason are the team captains for having the best dishes in the last challenge. Eboni's Blue Team includes Cate and Jeff; while Jason's Red Team includes Dino and Yachecia. They will cook two appetizers and two entr\u00e9es in a pop-up restaurant and the judges will determine the winning team based on guest feedback. The Red Team wins the challenge.\n* '''Challenge Winners/Immune:''' Dino Angelo Luciano, Jason Wang and Yachecia Holston\n* '''Pressure Test:''' Back at the MasterChef kitchen, the Blue Team members must make a chocolate souffl\u00e9 in 35 minutes.\n* '''Bottom three:''' Cate Meade, Eboni Henry and Jeff Philbin\n* The judges decide not to eliminate anyone, as all three contestants served perfect souffl\u00e9s.\n* '''Eliminated:''' None\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 18\n| Title           = Something Fishy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|9|13}}\n| Viewers         = 4.10<ref name=\"8.18&8.19\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-sept-13-2017/|title=\u2018America\u2019s Got Talent\u2019 adjusts up, \u2018Midnight, Texas\u2019 adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=September 15, 2017|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=September 15, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* '''Mystery Box Challenge:''' The six finalists faced a Mystery Box Challenge to cook a dish inspired by their family members. Eboni, Cate, and Yachecia delivered the top dishes with Cate winning.\n* '''Challenge Winner/Immune:''' Cate Meade\n* '''Elimination Challenge:''' As the winner of the Mystery Box Challenge, Cate assigned different time limits to the other contestants to cook dishes with salmon to join her in the semifinals: Jason got 60 minutes, Eboni had 50 minutes, Yachecia had 40 minutes, Dino had 30 minutes and Jeff had 20 minutes. Yachecia and Jeff were called out as the bottom.\n* '''Bottom two:''' Yachecia Holston and Jeff Philbin\n* The judges eliminated both Yachecia and Jeff.\n* '''Eliminated:''' Yachecia Holston and Jeff Philbin\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 19\n| Title           = The Semi-Finals\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|9|13}}\n| Viewers         = 4.10<ref name=\"8.18&8.19\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* '''Semi-Finals Skills Test 1:''' The contestants compete in a three-round Skills Test from each of the judges. The winner of each challenge will advance to the Finale. For the first round, Christina gave them a task to bake profiteroles in 45 minutes. Jason was the first contestant to advance in the Finals.\n* '''Winner:''' Jason Wang\n* '''Semi-Finals Skills Test 2:''' Aar\u00f3n challenged the remaining contestants in the 25-minute second round to bake a Latin-inspired molten lava cake and it was Eboni who won.\n* '''Winner:''' Eboni Henry\n*'''Bottom two:''' Dino Angelo Luciano and Cate Meade\n* '''Semi-Finals Skills Test 3:''' The last round tasked Dino and Cate to bake a cheese souffl\u00e9 by Gordon to secure the last place in the Finals. Dino won the round over Cate.\n* '''Winner:''' Dino Angelo Luciano\n* '''Eliminated:''' Cate Meade\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 20\n| Title           = The Finale, Pt. 1\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|9|20}}\n| Viewers         = 3.95<ref name=\"finale\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-sept-20-2017/|title=America\u2019s Got Talent,\u2019 \u2018Big Brother,\u2019 \u2018Masterchef\u2019 ajdust up, \u2018The Good Place\u2019 and \u2018Salvation\u2019 adjust down: Wednesday final ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=September 21, 2017|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=September 21, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* The judges are joined by former ''MasterChef'' judge [[Joe Bastianich]] for the judging of the finals. The three finalists will have one hour for each course to prepare four portions of their best appetizer, entr\u00e9e, and dessert. \n* '''Appetizer:''' Jason serves an uni custard with prawns, clams, and a miso vinaigrette. Eboni serves pan-seared scallops with charred romanesco, rainbow chard, and a pea pur\u00e9e. Dino serves squid ink capellini with calamari, clams, and cherry tomatoes.\n* The entr\u00e9es begin cooking as the first hour ends.\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 21\n| Title           = The Finale, Pt. 2\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|9|20}}\n| Viewers         = 3.95<ref name=\"finale\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = \n* '''Entr\u00e9e:''' Jason serves a tofu-skin wrapped black cod with bay scallops, maitake mushrooms, and a cucumber-pea tendril sauce. Dino serves rack of lamb on a lamb belly and sunchoke caponata with a balsamic glaze. Eboni serves a honey-glazed duck breast with sweet potato mash, collard greens and crispy heirloom carrots.\n* '''Dessert:''' Dino serves a roasted pistachio tiramisu with orange mascarpone cream, espresso caviar, and a pistachio tuile. Eboni serves a chocolate orbit cake with a macadamia crumble and a passion fruit coulis. Jason serves a black sesame japonaise with chocolate-yuzu mousse and berry-shiso coulis.\n* '''Final Three:''' Dino Angelo Luciano, Eboni Henry and Jason Wang\n* '''Winner Revealed:''' After reviewing all of the meals from the contestants, the judges name Dino the winner of this year's ''MasterChef'', winning him the $250,000, the trophy, and the cookbook deal.\n* '''MasterChef Winner:''' Dino Angelo Luciano\n|LineColor        = #64db88\n }}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{MasterChef (U.S.)}}\n\n[[Category:2017 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:MasterChef (American TV series)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television season\n |season_number = 8\n |bgcolour     = \n |image        = \n |caption      = \n |country      = United States\n |num_episodes = 21\n |network      = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n |first_aired  = {{Start date|2017|05|31}}\n |last_aired   = {{End date|2017|09|20}}\n |prev_season  = [[MasterChef (American season 7)|Season 7]]\n |next_season  = [[MasterChef (American season 9)|Season 9]]\n |episode_list = \n|}}\n\n'''Season 8''' of the American competitive [[reality television|reality TV]] series '''''[[MasterChef (American TV series)|MasterChef]]''''' premiered on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] on May 31, 2017.<ref name=\"futon\">{{cite web|title=FOX Announces Summer Premiere Dates|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2017/03/22/fox-announces-summer-premiere-dates-316121/20170322fox02/|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=April 4, 2017|date=March 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[Gordon Ramsay]] and [[Christina Tosi]] returned as judges. [[Aar\u00f3n Sanchez]] joined the cast this season as the third judge.<ref name=\"parade\">{{cite web|title=Chef Aar\u00f3n S\u00e1nchez Joins the MasterChef Judges' Panel |url=https://parade.com/548433/alison-ashton/chef-aaron-sanchez-joins-the-masterchef-judges-panel/|website=Parade|accessdate=April 25, 2017|date=February 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThis season was won by Dino Angelo Luciano with Eboni Henry and Jason Wang finishing as co-runners-up.\n\n==Top 20==\nSource for names, hometowns and occupations:<ref name=official-press-release-contestants>{{cite press release|url=http://www.fox.com/masterchef/article/meet-the-newest-batch-of-home-cooks| title=Meet the Newest Batch of Home Cooks|publisher= [[Fox Broadcasting]]|date= May 5, 2017|accessdate= June 11, 2017| archivedate= August 7, 2017| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20170807194436/http://www.fox.com/masterchef/article/meet-the-newest-batch-of-home-cooks}} Note: This supersedes an earlier press release with an incorrect name.</ref> Ages and nicknames as given on air.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#C1D8FF;\"\n! style=\"width:18%;\" |Contestant\n! style=\"width:4%;\"  |Age\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Hometown\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Occupation\n! style=\"width:16%;\" |Status\n|-\n| Dino Angelo Luciano\n| 28\n| [[Bensonhurst, New York]]\n| Dancer\n| style=\"background:green;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Winner September 20</span>\n|-\n| Eboni Henry\n| 33\n| [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| Addiction Counselor\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;\" rowspan=\"2\"|Runners-Up September 20\n|-\n| Jason Wang\n| 34\n| [[Newton, Massachusetts]]\